#EXTM3U
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tizen IPTV — aggregated channel playlist
#
# HOW THIS WORKS
#   The app loads this file by URL (Settings -> "M3U playlist URL"). Each
#   channel is two lines: an #EXTINF metadata line (name/logo/group — these
#   are PERMANENT, you never retype them) followed by the stream URL line.
#
#   Your stream URLs carry rotating tokens, e.g.:
#     https://<host>/<timestamp>/<hash>/<sig>/<slug>.m3u8
#   Only the URL line expires. When a stream dies:
#     1. Grab a fresh URL for that channel from your source.
#     2. Replace ONLY that channel's URL line below.
#     3. Commit / re-upload this file.
#     4. On the TV: Settings -> saved playlist -> Reload (or relaunch).
#   The names, logos, groups, and order stay put.
#
# HOSTING
#   Put this file somewhere with a stable, CORS-friendly URL and load the
#   raw link in the app. Good options: GitHub Gist/raw, Cloudflare Pages,
#   Netlify/Vercel static. (Avoid Dropbox/Drive direct links — fragile CORS.)
#   Rename to playlist.m3u when you publish it.
#
# FORMAT NOTES (matches js/playlist.js parser)
#   #EXTINF:-1 tvg-logo="<png url>" group-title="<section>",<Channel Name>
#   <stream url>
#   tvg-logo and group-title are optional. The text after the comma is the
#   channel name shown in the list.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

#EXTINF:-1 group-title="Sports",Fox Sports 1 4K
